This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it deals with mapping spoken language utterances to natural language understanding domains. It also involves the use of neural models and attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in NLP research. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) due to the use of neural models and classifiers. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) may also be a relevant sub-category as the paper deals with efficiently classifying spoken language utterances into specific domains. Finally, System and Control (cs.SD) may be a possible sub-category as the paper discusses practical constraints in real-time production systems.
